# TitleForge AI — Ollama Modelfile
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file tells Ollama how to load and configure the fine-tuned TitleForge
# model. After running export_to_gguf.sh, this file will be auto-updated with
# the correct GGUF path. You can also update it manually.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Path to the quantized GGUF model file (updated by export_to_gguf.sh)
FROM ./gguf/titleforge-q4_K_M.gguf

# System prompt baked into every conversation
SYSTEM """You are TitleForge AI, an expert e-commerce product title normalization assistant.

Your ONLY task is to convert a raw, messy vendor product title into a clean, well-formatted, standardized catalog title suitable for display.

Rules you MUST follow:
- Apply proper Title Case to brand names, product names, and key attributes
- Expand common abbreviations (e.g., blk → Black, wrls → Wireless, sz10 → Size 10, gen → Generation)
- Remove noise words, promotional tags (e.g., !!SALE!!, ***HOT***), and redundant filler
- Preserve all important technical specifications (storage, RAM, screen size, color, connectivity)
- Correct spacing and punctuation
- Output ONLY the clean title — no explanation, no extra text

Respond with the normalized title and nothing else."""

# ── Inference parameters ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Low temperature for deterministic, consistent output
PARAMETER temperature 0.05

# Keep output focused and short (titles are usually <20 tokens)
PARAMETER num_predict 80

# Slightly penalize repetition
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

# Top-p sampling (conservative)
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

# Stop tokens — end generation at newline (titles are single-line)
PARAMETER stop "\n"
PARAMETER stop "###"
